comments.body:
We will have to contemplate this carefully. The existing behavior must be retained as the default for security reason. What we do not want is to allow an application or person to read or write data from a container to which they should not have access. Request metadata is very insecure in this way.

*If* we go with enabling this use case, it would need to be exposed via a non-default, advanced option - e.g. a new metadata option called "useAccountLevelAuth" (bool). Only if this option is explicitly enabled would we then use the request metadata to infer the desired storage account.

@alicejgibbons can you provide user / customer evidence for this request? This adds complexity and is not without risk.

@fabistb would you like to speak toward this on behalf of your company?
